1
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:06,319
If I find a way out of this world

2
00:01:07,560 --> 00:01:08,879
Would you go back with me?

3
00:01:10,239 --> 00:01:11,719
I want to be with Xu Chi

4
00:01:13,319 --> 00:01:14,079
Wherever he is

5
00:01:15,120 --> 00:01:15,840
That's where I'll be

6
00:01:17,439 --> 00:01:18,760
So it turns out my world

7
00:01:19,480 --> 00:01:21,359
Is right within this tiny screen

8
00:01:25,280 --> 00:01:25,799
Yan Ying

9
00:01:27,239 --> 00:01:28,719
I think I've found the way out

10
00:01:44,359 --> 00:01:45,400
I made this for Xu Chi

11
00:01:45,599 --> 00:01:46,040
Mm-hmm

12
00:01:49,319 --> 00:01:49,760
Oh right

13
00:01:50,319 --> 00:01:51,439
On Qixi Festival

14
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:52,439
You stay home

15
00:01:52,760 --> 00:01:53,799
Xu Chi and I

16
00:01:54,319 --> 00:01:54,879
Have a date

17
00:01:58,760 --> 00:01:59,799
A while ago

18
00:02:00,959 --> 00:02:02,560
I learned a few new terms online

19
00:02:03,319 --> 00:02:04,280
One is called 'love-brained'

20
00:02:05,439 --> 00:02:06,560
And the other is 'PUA'

21
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:10,680
'Love-brained' refers to women

22
00:02:12,280 --> 00:02:14,159
Who, when falling in love,

23
00:02:15,039 --> 00:02:17,240
Make their partner their whole world,

24
00:02:17,719 --> 00:02:19,919
Unconditionally sacrificing everything for them

25
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:24,919
I thought it was just nonsense from the internet

26
00:02:27,879 --> 00:02:29,400
As for 'PUA'

27
00:02:30,599 --> 00:02:33,599
It means men treating women as toys or pets,

28
00:02:34,960 --> 00:02:36,479
Manipulating them emotionally

29
00:02:37,159 --> 00:02:38,080
So tell me

30
00:02:41,759 --> 00:02:42,759
Don't you think

31
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:45,439
Xu Chi is PUA-ing you?

32
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:47,319
So in your eyes

33
00:02:48,080 --> 00:02:49,039
I must be what they call

34
00:02:49,719 --> 00:02:50,919
'Love-brained'

35
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:52,080
Exactly

36
00:02:56,759 --> 00:02:57,120
Because I simply can't believe

37
00:02:58,599 --> 00:03:00,039
Someone as mighty as the Supreme Commander

38
00:03:00,159 --> 00:03:01,960
Of Qingyun Kingdom’s armies

39
00:03:01,960 --> 00:03:03,840
Would actually be in a kitchen doing this for a man

40
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:06,520
Your hands

41
00:03:07,400 --> 00:03:08,599
Are the hands that wield the Luoying Spear

42
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:10,319
The hands that slay foes

43
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:13,879
But definitely not hands to make soup for a man in a kitchen

44
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:22,159
Who says

45
00:03:22,479 --> 00:03:23,800
The hands that wield the Luoying Spear

46
00:03:24,560 --> 00:03:25,800
Guess we can't make soup anymore.

47
00:03:26,879 --> 00:03:27,520
These two things

48
00:03:27,919 --> 00:03:28,840
don't seem related, do they?

49
00:03:29,199 --> 00:03:30,879
This isn't something you should be doing.

50
00:03:32,080 --> 00:03:32,520
Yan Ying,

51
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:35,759
I'm the one who knows you best.

52
00:03:37,360 --> 00:03:38,199
But now, you've changed so much

53
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:39,719
that I barely recognize you.

54
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:49,840
When Father died in battle,

55
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:52,280
I had just turned fifteen.

56
00:03:55,560 --> 00:03:56,960
I didn't even have time to grieve

57
00:03:58,199 --> 00:03:59,879
before I was thrust onto the battlefield.

58
00:04:01,159 --> 00:04:02,520
I inherited Father's legacy,

59
00:04:04,080 --> 00:04:06,039
becoming a renowned female general.

60
00:04:06,199 --> 00:04:07,639
That was my childhood dream.

61
00:04:09,319 --> 00:04:10,159
So,

62
00:04:11,439 --> 00:04:12,319
in my heart,

63
00:04:12,680 --> 00:04:14,280
I had to carry the weight of the world—

64
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:15,840
the nation,

65
00:04:16,279 --> 00:04:17,120
and the people.

66
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:19,720
But the one thing

67
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:22,639
I couldn't have was myself.

68
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:25,199
So you mean, now,

69
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:27,800
you finally have yourself?

70
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:29,040
Is that it?

71
00:04:29,959 --> 00:04:31,839
Becoming a renowned female general

72
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,120
and being

73
00:04:34,560 --> 00:04:36,079
a normal person who longs for happiness

74
00:04:36,759 --> 00:04:38,360
are just different choices for different times.

75
00:04:39,759 --> 00:04:40,639
But the key is,

76
00:04:41,839 --> 00:04:43,120
I have the right to choose.

77
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:48,000
I can choose the life I want to live,

78
00:04:50,519 --> 00:04:51,560
and I can also choose

79
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:54,639
the person I want to love.

80
00:04:57,639 --> 00:04:58,759
Can I do that too?

81
00:05:05,720 --> 00:05:06,199
Look,

82
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:07,560
does it look good?

83
00:05:12,120 --> 00:05:13,279
I agree, it doesn’t look great.

84
00:05:14,759 --> 00:05:15,720
But Xu Chi,

85
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:17,720
he’ll like it.

86
00:05:45,439 --> 00:05:46,319
Don’t worry, boss.

87
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:48,759
The server control room is now manned 24/7.

88
00:05:49,040 --> 00:05:49,839
Unless something unexpected happens,

89
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:52,160
the server absolutely won’t update.

90
00:05:53,279 --> 00:05:53,480
Good.

91
00:05:55,920 --> 00:05:57,319
Happy Valentine’s Day!

92
00:06:04,360 --> 00:06:06,279
Yay, I won!

93
00:06:06,759 --> 00:06:07,839
I'm so impressive!

94
00:06:07,839 --> 00:06:08,959
This is my first time playing, and I'm already this good!

95
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:15,240
Weird...

96
00:06:15,759 --> 00:06:16,839
Why does it feel like...

97
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:19,040
I've done this before?

98
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:27,759
One, two, three...

99
00:06:27,759 --> 00:06:29,000
Just three moves!

100
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:29,920
You're definitely going to lose!

101
00:06:29,920 --> 00:06:31,800
You mocked me after just two moves?

102
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:33,040
You’re not much better yourself!

103
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:35,519
Why do I feel like...

104
00:06:35,519 --> 00:06:37,000
this place seems so familiar?

105
00:06:38,639 --> 00:06:40,000
Like I've been here before?

106
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:51,759
Sometimes...

107
00:06:52,439 --> 00:06:53,800
memories like to mess with people.

108
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:57,319
Many things feel familiar for a reason...

109
00:06:57,959 --> 00:06:59,279
but forgetting is real too.

110
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:02,560
Some people forget their past...

111
00:07:04,040 --> 00:07:05,160
even the ones they love.

112
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:09,800
How sad...

113
00:07:14,680 --> 00:07:15,759
for those who are forgotten.

114
00:07:16,439 --> 00:07:17,240
It's really heartbreaking.

115
00:07:20,160 --> 00:07:20,800
But...

116
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:23,120
it must also be painful...

117
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:26,000
for the ones who lose their memories.

118
00:07:32,040 --> 00:07:32,839
Still, as long as...

119
00:07:33,279 --> 00:07:35,079
one of them remembers the other...

120
00:07:36,199 --> 00:07:37,800
their love won't disappear.

121
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:40,639
So, do you think...

122
00:07:41,439 --> 00:07:43,399
she will fall in love with him again?

123
00:07:44,759 --> 00:07:45,600
What do you think?

124
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:47,360
She will.

125
00:07:52,199 --> 00:07:53,000
Oh, by the way...

126
00:07:58,040 --> 00:07:58,720
Ah!

127
00:07:58,720 --> 00:07:59,959
It’s all broken...

128
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:02,759
I worked so hard to make that!

129
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:06,480
It's okay...

130
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:07,319
I'll take it as it is.

131
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:21,000
I have a gift for you too.

132
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:23,399
Close your eyes.

133
00:08:28,399 --> 00:08:29,040
Are you ready?

134
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:29,879
Yes.

135
00:08:31,079 --> 00:08:31,399
Three...

136
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:32,519
Two...

137
00:08:33,399 --> 00:08:33,600
One...

138
00:08:40,159 --> 00:08:40,639
Wow!

139
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:42,320
It's the Milky Way

140
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:44,080
That's right

141
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:45,759
It's the Milky Way

142
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:47,279
Over there

143
00:08:47,799 --> 00:08:49,759
There's a planet named after you

144
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:51,639
It's like a light in the Milky Way

145
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:55,360
This star

146
00:08:55,799 --> 00:08:57,360
Took tens of thousands of years

147
00:08:57,360 --> 00:08:58,240
To reach us

148
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:00,639
It's like me in the Milky Way

149
00:09:00,879 --> 00:09:02,240
Saying 'I love you' to you

150
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:05,000
By the time you hear it

151
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:08,159
I've already loved you for a long time

152
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:09,840
A very long time

153
00:09:15,039 --> 00:09:15,840
So

154
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:19,559
Can you tell me now

155
00:09:22,039 --> 00:09:23,519
Who has been forgotten?

156
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:29,000
Is it you?
